Scorecard Structure
Scorecards evaluate entities against rules organized into levels. Each rule checks specific conditions (properties, relations, or scorecard criteria), and passing rules at different levels determines your overall scorecard level.

🎯 Level System
Levels work as progressive tiers - you must pass rules at lower levels to achieve higher ones. Common level patterns I see in your service:

Pattern 1: Metal Tiers (Bronze → Silver → Gold)
Bronze: Basic requirements (easiest)
Silver: Intermediate standards
Gold: Excellence standards (hardest)
Pattern 2: Performance Tiers (Low → Medium → High → Elite)
Progressive performance benchmarks
Pattern 3: Traffic Light (Red → Yellow → Orange → Green)
Risk-based assessment
Pattern 4: Descriptive (Basic → Good → Great)
Maturity-based progression
